{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> δοξ-άζω</b>, <br /> <b>think, imagine,</b> with <i>accusative</i> et <i>infinitive</i>,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" A.Ag. 673, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Supplices” 1043, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; with <i>double</i> <i>accusative</i>, πῶς ταῦτ᾽ ἀληθῆ.. δοξάσ; how <b>can I suppose</b> this to be true? [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Choephori” 844; δ. βελτίους ἑαυτούς 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Philebus” 48e; τὰ εὔχρηστα τῶν ζῴων θεοὺς ἐδόξασαν 3rd c.AD(?): Diogenes Laertius 1.11; also _absolutely_, μετ᾽ ἀσφαλείας δ. 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.120 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; δοξάζων μὲν οὔ not <b>expecting</b> it, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 545:\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] —<i>passive</i>, δ. εἶναι <b>to be supposed</b> to be, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Timaeus” 46d, +others\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὅση δοξάζεται (i.e. εἶναι) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Phd.” 108c; δ. κακοί [prev. author] “Lg.” 646e; δ. δίκαιος [prev. author] “R.” 588b; τὰ δοξαζόμενα [prev. author] “Plt.” 278b. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> with <i>participle</i>, δοξάσει τις ἀκούων <b>will suppose that</b> he hears, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Supplices” 60 (Lyric poetry). \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> with <i>accusative</i> <i>cognate</i>, δόξας δ. <b>entertain</b> opinions, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Crito” 46d \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; δ. ψευδῆ <b>hold</b> false <b>opinions,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Tht.” 189c; ψευδῶς δοξαζόμενα Polystr. p.26W. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> <i>absolutely</i>, <b>form</b> or <b>hold an opinion,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Ph